	            	                            <h2 itemprop="headline" class="font">
                    How to Apply                </h2>
            	<div class="page-header">
							</div>
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
		
		
	
	
	<div itemprop="articleBody">
		<p>Online application process - a personalised approach</p>
 
<p>Our students come from a variety of different backgrounds, which is why we treat each applicant as an individual. Our online application form guides you through a series of steps designed to help us get to know you, and determine whether you would be a good fit for your chosen programme.</p>
<p>Our team of Enrollment Advisors is on hand to help you at any stage of the application process, whether you need advice on choosing a programme that fits your interests and career goals, or you need help answering a question on the form.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><br />How to Apply:</p>
<p>Check the entry requirements, start dates, fees and financing options with contact us.<br />Download the ‘how to apply’ guide and start the application <br />Submit supporting documents<br />Await Board of Admissions decision<br />Confirm your place and choose a payment plan</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><br />entry requirements</p>
<p> </p>
<p><br />Each of our online programmes has specific entry requirements which you will find on the relevant programme with contact us. In your application you need to demonstrate that you meet these criteria.</p>
<p>Please choose your preferred start date. We recommend you submit your application at least one month prior to your preferred start date so that we have enough time to process your application.</p>
<p>You will find information about payment plans and possible funding sources, as well as the tuition fees* for your programme on the Fees and funding contact us.</p>
<p>*Be aware that there is a separate, non-refundable application fee.</p>
<p>IMAT is necessary for medicine and dentistry volunteers.</p>
<p>Score of academic IELTS should be minimum 7 for international students.</p>	</div>

	
